# Physics Classroom - Project Architecture

This is a **Next.js 15** TypeScript application for online physics education with assignment management and question banking.

## Core Technology Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 15 with App Router + React 19 + TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components + Radix UI primitives  
- **Database**: Supabase (PostgreSQL) with real-time features
- **Authentication**: NextAuth.js v5 with Supabase adapter
- **AI Integration**: OpenAI API for question generation and grading
- **Math Rendering**: KaTeX for mathematical expressions

## Directory Structure

```
src/
├── app/                     # Next.js App Router pages
│   ├── admin/              # Admin-only pages (assignments, question bank)
│   ├── api/                # API routes (question-bank, grading, etc.)
│   ├── assignments/        # Student assignment pages
│   ├── auth/               # Authentication pages
│   ├── dashboard/          # User dashboard
│   └── lessons/            # Lesson content pages
├── components/             # React components
│   ├── admin/              # Admin-specific components
│   ├── assignment-builder/ # Assignment creation tools
│   ├── assignment-taking/  # Student assignment interface
│   ├── question-bank/      # Question bank management
│   ├── student/            # Student-specific components
│   └── ui/                 # shadcn/ui base components
├── contexts/               # React Context providers
│   ├── AssignmentContext.tsx
│   └── QuestionBankContext.tsx
├── data/                   # Static data (physics units, sample questions)
├── lib/                    # Shared utilities and configurations
├── types/                  # TypeScript type definitions
└── utils/                  # Utility functions
```

